2891:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h **** /**
2892:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   * @brief  Perform basic configuration of USART for enabling use in Multi processor Mode
2893:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         (several USARTs connected in a network, one of the USARTs can be the master,
2894:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         its TX output connected to the RX inputs of the other slaves USARTs).
2895:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   * @note   In MultiProcessor mode, the following bits must be kept cleared:
2896:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *           - LINEN bit in the USART_CR2 register,
2897:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *           - CLKEN bit in the USART_CR2 register,
2898:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *           - SCEN bit in the USART_CR3 register,
2899:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *           - IREN bit in the USART_CR3 register,
2900:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *           - HDSEL bit in the USART_CR3 register.
2901:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   * @note   Call of this function is equivalent to following function call sequence :
2902:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         - Clear LINEN in CR2 using @ref LL_USART_DisableLIN() function
2903:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         - Clear CLKEN in CR2 using @ref LL_USART_DisableSCLKOutput() function
2904:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         - Clear SCEN in CR3 using @ref LL_USART_DisableSmartcard() function
2905:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         - Clear IREN in CR3 using @ref LL_USART_DisableIrda() function
2906:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         - Clear HDSEL in CR3 using @ref LL_USART_DisableHalfDuplex() function
2907:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   * @note   Other remaining configurations items related to Multi processor Mode
2908:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         (as Baud Rate, Wake Up Method, Node address, ...) should be set using
2909:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         dedicated functions
2910:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   * @rmtoll CR2          LINEN         LL_USART_ConfigMultiProcessMode\n
2911:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         CR2          CLKEN         LL_USART_ConfigMultiProcessMode\n
2912:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         CR3          SCEN          LL_USART_ConfigMultiProcessMode\n
2913:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         CR3          HDSEL         LL_USART_ConfigMultiProcessMode\n
2914:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         CR3          IREN          LL_USART_ConfigMultiProcessMode
2915:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   * @param  USARTx USART Instance
